question_text:
A 3×3 matrix contains shapes in each cell. The bottom-right cell is missing.

**Row 1:**
- Cell (1,1): {"shapes": [{"type": "triangle", "count": 1, "fill": "filled", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}
- Cell (1,2): {"shapes": [{"type": "triangle", "count": 2, "fill": "filled", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}
- Cell (1,3): {"shapes": [{"type": "triangle", "count": 3, "fill": "filled", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}

**Row 2:**
- Cell (2,1): {"shapes": [{"type": "circle", "count": 1, "fill": "outline", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}
- Cell (2,2): {"shapes": [{"type": "circle", "count": 2, "fill": "outline", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}
- Cell (2,3): {"shapes": [{"type": "circle", "count": 3, "fill": "outline", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}

**Row 3:**
- Cell (3,1): {"shapes": [{"type": "square", "count": 1, "fill": "striped", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}
- Cell (3,2): {"shapes": [{"type": "square", "count": 2, "fill": "striped", "orientation_degrees": 0, "position": "center"}]}
- Cell (3,3): **MISSING**

Which option correctly completes cell (3,3)?
